#. <section class="sutta" id="sn22.4"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn22.4:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 22"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 22"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.4:0.2"
msgid "1. Nakulapituvagga"
msgstr "1. Nakula’s Father"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn22.4:0.3"
msgid "4. Dutiyahāliddikānisutta"
msgstr "4. Hāliddikāni (2nd)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.13"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.4:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "sn22.4:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā mahākaccāno avantīsu viharati kuraraghare papāte pabbate."
msgstr ""
"At one time Venerable Mahākaccāna was staying in the land of the Avantis "
"near Kuraraghara on Steep Mountain."

msgctxt "sn22.4:1.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho hāliddikāni gahapati yenāyasmā mahākaccāno … pe … ekamantaṃ nisinno "
"kho hāliddikāni gahapati āyasmantaṃ mahākaccānaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then the householder Hāliddikāni went up to Venerable Mahākaccāna … and said "
"to him:"

msgctxt "sn22.4:1.4"
msgid "“vuttamidaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā sakkapañhe:"
msgstr "“Sir, this was said by the Buddha in ‘The Questions of Sakka’:"

msgctxt "sn22.4:1.5"
msgid ""
"‘ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā taṇhāsaṅkhayavimuttā, te accantaniṭṭhā "
"accantayogakkhemino accantabrahmacārino accantapariyosānā seṭṭhā "
"devamanussānan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Those ascetics and brahmins who are freed due to the ending of craving have "
"reached the ultimate goal, the ultimate sanctuary, the ultimate spiritual "
"life, the ultimate end, and are best among gods and humans.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.4:2.1"
msgid ""
"Imassa nu kho, bhante, bhagavatā saṅkhittena bhāsitassa kathaṃ vitthārena "
"attho daṭṭhabbo”ti?"
msgstr ""
"How should we see the detailed meaning of the Buddha’s brief statement?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.4:3.1"
msgid ""
"“Rūpadhātuyā kho, gahapati, yo chando yo rāgo yā nandī yā taṇhā ye "
"upayupādānā cetaso adhiṭṭhānābhinivesānusayā, tesaṃ khayā virāgā nirodhā "
"cāgā paṭinissaggā ‘cittaṃ suvimuttanti’ vuccati."
msgstr ""
"“Householder, consider any desire, greed, relishing, and craving for the "
"form element; any attraction, grasping, mental dedication, insistence, and "
"underlying tendencies. With the ending, fading away, cessation, giving away, "
"and letting go of that, the mind is said to be ‘well freed’."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.4:4.1"
msgid "Vedanādhātuyā kho, gahapati …"
msgstr ""
"Consider any desire, greed, relishing, and craving for the feeling element …"

msgctxt "sn22.4:4.2"
msgid "saññādhātuyā kho, gahapati …"
msgstr "the perception element …"

msgctxt "sn22.4:4.3"
msgid "saṅkhāradhātuyā kho, gahapati …"
msgstr "the choices element …"

msgctxt "sn22.4:4.4"
msgid ""
"viññāṇadhātuyā kho, gahapati, yo chando yo rāgo yā nandī yā taṇhā ye "
"upayupādānā cetaso adhiṭṭhānābhinivesānusayā, tesaṃ khayā virāgā nirodhā "
"cāgā paṭinissaggā ‘cittaṃ suvimuttanti’ vuccati."
msgstr ""
"the consciousness element; any attraction, grasping, mental dedication, "
"insistence, and underlying tendencies. With the ending, fading away, "
"cessation, giving away, and letting go of that, the mind is said to be ‘well "
"freed’."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.4:5.1"
msgid "Iti kho, gahapati, yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ bhagavatā sakkapañhe:"
msgstr ""
"So, householder, that’s how to understand the detailed meaning of what the "
"Buddha said in brief in ‘The Questions of Sakka’:"

msgctxt "sn22.4:5.2"
msgid ""
"‘ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā taṇhāsaṅkhayavimuttā te accantaniṭṭhā "
"accantayogakkhemino accantabrahmacārino accantapariyosānā seṭṭhā "
"devamanussānan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Those ascetics and brahmins who are freed due to the ending of craving have "
"reached the ultimate goal, the ultimate sanctuary, the ultimate spiritual "
"life, the ultimate end, and are best among gods and humans.’”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.4:6.1"
msgid ""
"Imassa kho, gahapati, bhagavatā saṅkhittena bhāsitassa evaṃ vitthārena attho "
"daṭṭhabbo”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn22.4:6.2"
msgid "Catutthaṃ."
msgstr ""
